Hi! My roommate and I are moving to a different location and are planning to give up the last 11-12 months of our lease in mid-late August (and arrange a lease takeover with our property management group).<br>
<br>
Our place is on Monument Ave, a few minutes from Bon Secours St. Mary's Hospital. It's a 3 bedroom, 2 bath, 1,428 square feet house. It has a large, fenced yard, off-street parking, a storage shed, and allows dogs with a pet deposit and a $25/month pet fee. The rent is $2,200/month without utilities. Utilities (water, sewer, trash, electric, internet) usually run us about $200/month in summer.<br>
<br>
If you're interested in learning more and/or arranging a tour, let me know! Also, we're willing to sell certain pieces of furniture too if you're interested! Happy to answer any questions! Thanks!
    </section>

